President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 17-23, 2015 as Emergency Medical Services Week in the United States. In his proclamation, he recognizes the crucial role that emergency medical services (EMS) professionals play in providing care during medical emergencies. These professionals include 911 dispatchers, emergency medical technicians, paramedics, EMS medical directors, law enforcement officers, firefighters, and nurses. President Obama commends the selfless dedication of these individuals who often operate as volunteers and risk their own lives and health to protect others. He emphasizes the importance of having an efficient and high-quality EMS system to ensure care during any emergency. The proclamation encourages all Americans to show their support for their local EMS providers and take steps to improve their personal safety and preparedness.